==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sonneteer
<hw>Son`net*eer"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A composer of
sonnets, or small poems; a small poet; -- usually in contempt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What woful stuff this madrigal would be⟦br⟧
In some starved hackney <qex>sonneteer</qex> or me!</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sonneteer</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sonneteer
<hw>Son`net*eer"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To compose sonnets.</def>
<rj><au>Lowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sonneter</ent>⟦br⟧
